\par \pard\plain \widctlpar \f5\fs20 CDWAV can use three different methods to handle incoming wave data during a recording. The default setting is the best in terms of reliability and performance, but I\rquote ve seen a system where this method didn\rquote 
t function at all, resulting in a complete lockup of the program. The middle setting can fix this problem, and the left setting is intended as a last resort, but should work on any system.
\par For insiders, the default method (max performance) sends acknowledges directly to the thread. The middle option uses a callback function, which in turn will send the message to t
he thread. The max compatibility setting uses window messages to communicate with the driver, and causes the most overhead.
